       <h3>
        <a href="/news/index.php">
         News
        </a>
       </h3>
       <ul class="rss-list">
        <li>
         <h4>
          <a href="https://hsp.utah.edu/news/hurley-wins-second.php">
           <img alt="jazmine hurley" src="https://hsp.utah.edu/_images/jazmine-hurley-thumb.jpg">
            Jazmine Hurley wins second place at CSBS Research Day
           </img>
          </a>
         </h4>
         <p>
          Jazmine Hurley; Health, Society &amp; Policy senior won second place at the CSBS Research Day. Upon her anticipated graduation in Fall 2018, Hurley plans to pursue a master’s degree in Public Health. The title of the research project is "Experiencing intimate partner violence (IPV) directly affects the mental, emotional, sexual, and physical health of the victim.”
         </p>
        </li>
        <li>
         <h4>
          <a href="https://csbs.utah.edu/news/kutv-projectembrace.php">
           <img alt="Mohan Sudabattula" src="https://csbs.utah.edu/_images/mohan1-thumb.png">
            Pay it Forward: Nonprofit collects medical equipment for disadvantaged around the world
           </img>
          </a>
         </h4>
         <p>
          HSP student Mohan Sudabattula was recently featured on the KUTV 2 News Pay it Forward segment for his nonprofit organization Project Embrace.  Sudabattula received a donation of $500 from Mountain America Credit Union to help Project Embrace with supplies, trips, and more.
         </p>
        </li>
        <li>
         <h4>
          <a href="https://hsp.utah.edu/news/james-house-lecture.php">
